  <div class="editable-message-body">
    <div class="comment-text editable-message-text" itemprop="commentText"><p>I&#x27;m sorry but that doesn&#x27;t fix the security bug at all. It doesn&#x27;t fix the permissions if they are currently bad, and even if the .Xauthority file doesn&#x27;t exist, fopen() won&#x27;t do better than set_file_<wbr />contents(<wbr />). Actually checking for the return code of the function might have helped too, but anyway.</p>
<p>In any case, care should be taken to:</p>
<p>- fix the permissions of existing .Xauthority files in a secure way<br />
- correctly set the umask (or use a function which does it) before writing a new file</p></div>
    
    
    
